731750f.title: Fires, accidents and tragedies - [Collapse of a building caused by tornado.]
731750f.text:
The collapse of a building under construction at West 136th Street
and Riverside Drive; caused by a Tornado at 2 p.m.
June 26, 1905.
Gustav Scholer, M.D.
MAY BE REPRODUCED.
731750f.folder: 136th Street and Riverside Drive, Manhattan, N.Y.

722801f-a.title: Manhattan: Riverside Drive - 136th Street
722801f-a.text:
Riverside Drive, east aide, north from 138th to and including
137th Streets, showinm the collapse of building under construction,
due to a tornado, in which one person was killed and two injured.
June 26, 1905.
MAY BE REPRODUCED.
